<p>To refresh all the passwords on your Mac, you need to remove all the instances of your old BYU-I password. This tutorial shows the quickest way of doing this:</p>
<ol>
<li>Click "Finder", "Applications", "Utilities", and then "Keychain Access", as indicated in the picture below.
<div><img src="Images/helpdesk/Apple%20remove%20keychain%20passwords/mac_picture1.jpg" /></div>
</li>
<br /><br />
<li>Type in "byui" in the search field, as shown in the picture below.
<div><img src="Images/helpdesk/Apple%20remove%20keychain%20passwords/mac_picture2.jpg" /></div>
</li>
<br /><br />
<li>Hold down the shift key, click on the bottom one, then press the delete key, to get the result shown in the picture below.
<div><img src="Images/helpdesk/Apple%20remove%20keychain%20passwords/mac_picture3.jpg" /></div>
</li>
<br /><br /> </ol>
<p>If you have more computers, return to the "more computers" Operating System (OS) menu. Otherwise, continue to the change password instructions.</p>
